			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Adimab is looking for an experienced bioengineer to join its team.&nbsp; The successful candidate will be responsible for optimizing Adimab&rsquo;s yeast platform and developing additional capabilities for high-throughput production of antibodies and antigens.</p>
<p>
Responsibilities</p>
<ul>
<li>
Plan, execute, and supervise yeast-based recombinant protein expression and purification activities</li>
<li>
Lead process development activities for improved recombinant yeast production characteristics</li>
<li>
Develop and implement high-throughput and automated strategies to improve upon the throughput and efficiency of production workflows</li>
<li>
Troubleshoot, engineer, and optimize production characteristics in fungal and microbial production hosts</li>
<li>
Actively collaborate with other technical groups to develop improved recombinant production systems</li>
<li>
Develop and improve upon the production of monoclonal antibodies and antigens</li>
<li>
Oversee the scientific work of 2-3 research associates</li>
<li>
Support process technology transfer and external project management initiatives</li>
</ul>
<p>
Qualifications</p>
<ul>
<li>
Ph.D. with 2-5 years (or M.S. in biochemistry with 8+ years) in an industrial biopharmaceutical, CMO, or biotechnology bioprocess R&amp;D setting</li>
<li>
Team player with exceptional communication skills and demonstrated ability to perform at a high level in a fast-paced results-oriented environment</li>
<li>
Requires a depth of technical knowledge in yeast/microbial physiology, medium development, and bioprocess development approaches for improved recombinant protein attributes</li>
<li>
General expertise in scale-up/scale-down principles, predictive modeling, process analytics for fungal production of recombinant proteins</li>
</ul>
<p>
Preferred Qualifications</p>
<ul>
<li>
Functional expertise with affinity and non-affinity protein chromatography purification methods</li>
<li>
Expertise in the cultivation and recombinant expression across a diverse panel of production hosts&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Technical depth of experience with production, harvest, filtration, analytical methods, and purification equipment and operations</li>
<li>
Functional knowledge of design of experiments (DoE) and statistical data analysis methodologies</li>
<li>
Experience supervising direct reports</li>
<li>
Experience in managing external projects</li>
<li>
Familiarity with mammalian and insect production systems</li>
<li>
Familiarity with automated liquid handling technologies</li>
</ul>
<p>
Adimab conducts antibody drug discovery for the world&#39;s top pharmaceutical companies.&nbsp; Adimab&#39;s yeast-based monoclonal antibody discovery platform functions like a synthetic human immune system to create novel antibody therapeutics across a broad range of diseases from cancer and autoimmune diseases to serious infectious diseases. Adimab is backed by top-tier venture capitalist firms including Google Ventures, OrbiMed Advisors, Polaris Venture Partners, SV Life Sciences, and Borealis Ventures.</p>
<p>
Located in New Hampshire&rsquo;s beautiful Upper Connecticut River Valley, Adimab is minutes from Dartmouth College, the Geisel School of Medicine, the Thayer School of Engineering, the Tuck School of Business, and Dartmouth-Hitchcock Medical Center.&nbsp; Situated near the Appalachian Trail, the area is renowned for its premier skiing, hiking, canoeing, and kayaking.</p>
<p>
Adimab offers individually tailored compensation packages comprised of competitive salary, bonus, and equity components, in addition to a world class working environment in a newly constructed lab.</p>
