Adimab is looking for experienced research associates to join its team.&nbsp; Successful candidates will support Adimab&#39;s novel antibody discovery, maturation, and production platform by performing core laboratory services, maintaining laboratory stocks, and taking on other responsibilities that may arise at a growing biotech company. This position reports to the Laboratory Manager.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Specific tasks may include:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Operate and maintain sequencing and PCR instruments</li>
<li>
Operate automation equipment according to standard protocols</li>
<li>
Assist with purchasing and maintenance of laboratory supplies and equipment</li>
<li>
Troubleshoot and calibrate instruments</li>
<li>
Prepare reagents, buffers, and&nbsp; media</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
B.S. with experience in molecular biology, biochemistry, or a related field</li>
<li>
1&ndash;3 years of laboratory experience</li>
<li>
Experience with PCR and Sanger sequencing technology</li>
<li>
Demonstrated ability to work within defined standard operating procedures</li>
<li>
Experience using Excel and knowledge of basic chemical calculations</li>
<li>
Comfortable and productive in a fast paced environment of ambiguity and change&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Detail oriented and well organized</li>
<li>
Strong customer service and communication skills</li>
<li>
An excellent team player, who also is able to work independently where appropriate</li>
<li>
Positive attitude and source of energy to all employees&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>
Adimab conducts antibody drug discovery for the world&#39;s top pharmaceutical companies.&nbsp; Adimab&#39;s yeast-based monoclonal antibody discovery platform functions like a synthetic human immune system to create novel antibody therapeutics across a broad range of diseases from cancer and autoimmune diseases to serious infectious diseases. Adimab is backed by top-tier venture capitalist firms including Google Ventures, OrbiMed Advisors, Polaris Venture Partners, SV Life Sciences, and Borealis Ventures.</p>
<p>
Located in New Hampshire&rsquo;s beautiful Upper Connecticut River Valley, Adimab is minutes from Dartmouth College, the Geisel School of Medicine, the Thayer School of Engineering, the Tuck School of Business, and Dartmouth-Hitchcock Medical Center.&nbsp; Situated near the Appalachian Trail, the area is renowned for its premier skiing, hiking, canoeing, and kayaking.</p>
